ਅਸੀਂ ਹਵਾ , ਪਾਣੀ , ਧਰਤ , ਆਕਾਸ਼ , ਪਸ਼ੂ-ਪੰਛੀ ਕਿਸੇ ਨਾਲ ਵੀ ਇਨਸਾਫ ਨਹੀਂ ਕੀਤਾ , ਪਰ ਪੂਰੀ ਕਾਇਨਾਤ ਫਿਰ ਵੀ ਇਨਸਾਨ ਦਾ ਮੋਹ ਭਰਿਆ ਫਿਕਰ ਕਰਦੀ ਜਾਪ ਰਹੀ ਹੈ ।। ਸਾਡੀਆਂ ਕੁਦਰਤ ਨਾਲ ਕੀਤੀਆਂ ਹਰਕਤਾਂ ਦੇ ਬਾਵਜੂਦ ਕੁਦਰਤ ਦਾ ਹਰ ਜੀਵ-ਜੰਤੂ , ਪੇੜ-ਪੌਦਾ ਤੇ ਧਰਤ-ਆਕਾਸ਼ ਸਾਡੀ ਖ਼ੈਰ ਮੰਗਦੇ ਹੋਏ ਰੱਬ ਨੂੰ ਪੁੱਛ ਰਹੇ ਨੇ , ਸੁੱਖ ਤਾਂ ਹੈ ?

When rice is left over we mostly make fodanicha bhat or bhatach thalipeeth. Today we will see one more tasty, easy and quick recipe that will help to finish off the left over rice in a jiffy. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.

Ingredients:
• Left over Rice
• Green chilies
• 4~5 Garlic cloves
• Water
• Salt to taste
• 2 tsp Corn flour
• 1/4 tsp Cumin seeds
• Chopped red Capsicum
• Chopped green Capsicum
• Finely grated Carrot
• Finely chopped Coriander leaves
• Oil

Method:
• Transfer the left over rice into a blender jar. 
• Add green chili, garlic, water and blend everything into smooth 
   batter. 
• Transfer the batter into a bowl. 
• Add salt, corn flour, cumin seeds, red capsicum, green capsicum, 
  grated carrot, coriander leaves and mix everything well together. 
• You can use wheat flour, maida, rice flour in place of corn flour. 
  You can add veggies of your choice. 
• Batter is ready.  
• Heat up a pan on medium heat. 
• Brush a little oil in the pan. 
• Spread the batter on the pan to make small ghavane. 
• When lower side is roasted well flip over and roast well from other 
  side too. 
• When both sides are roasted well take the ghavane off into a dish. 
• You can have these dose with chutney or sauce or as it is. 
• This can be a good lunch box option for your kids.

Timane is a very easy and simple recipe. This healthy recipe is light on stomach. You can try this recipe as a healthy breakfast or evening snack too. This is Vidarbha special recipe made from only moong dal. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.

Ingredients:
• 1/2 cup Moong dal
• 2~3 chopped Green chilies
• 7~8 chopped Garlic cloves
• A little Water
• 1/4 tsp Turmeric powder
• Salt to taste
• Finely chopped Coriander leaves (Optional)
• Oil

Method:
• Wash moong dal really good 2-3 times with water. 
• Soak the dal in enough water for about 6-7 hours or overnight. 
• Transfer the soaked moong dal into a blender jar and add green chilies, garlic, water and blend 
  into smooth paste. 
• Transfer the paste into a bowl. 
• Add a little water to adjust the consistency. The batter should have pouring consistency.
• Add turmeric powder, salt and mix everything well together. 
• Add coriander leaves and mix well.
• Coriander leaves are optional. You can skip it if you don’t want. 
• Heat up a pan on medium heat. 
• Brush a little oil on it.
• Add the batter at the center of the pan and spread it evenly. 
• Spread a little oil along the edges. 
• When lower side gets nice golden color spread a little oil on the upper side of timane. 
• Flip the timane over and roast well from other side too. 
• When it is roasted well from other side too fold it and take it off the pan into a dish. 
• Timane is all ready. 
• You can have them as it is or with chutney or sauce too. 
• Another way is, spread peanut chutney, roll it and enjoy.
